	<p>Hmmm, all I can say is if they ever implement something like this they had better also put in a way to disable or prevent it. As buggy as things are I can just see geting a credit card bill with $300 worth of wrong or bugged player-to-player cash transfers. As apathetic as the credit card companies have become about doing automated business I'd be afraid to have a credit card of mine tied into a system like this unwillingly. Or even worse how about the parents who pay for a kids account. I can see a scam artist talking a 10 year old into "just go ahead and authorize this..."<br />
Scarry stuff.</p>
	
	
	
