	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I can't belive they'd ever implement this.  I'd <u>like</u> to believe it's because they care too much about the integrity of their product.  But I can no longer make that statement.  I still, however, don't believe they'll do it, albeit for a less virtuous reason - server rollbacks.  <br />
<br />
Say I buy a pair of flayed barbarianskin leggings (sorry to all my shaman brothers from the north  <img src="images/smilies/tongue.gif" border="0" alt="" title="stick out tongue" smilieid="6" /> ) for 100 RL dollars for my monk, and the server crashes 12 seconds after that.  They might roll us back to a state where I don't have the leggings.  SOE controls the state of EQ, but they couldn't roll back the charge to the credit card company.  <br />
<br />
Actually, I suppose they could try to log such before-and-after problems, and process credits to the credit card companies to compensate for rolled-back purchases.  But I can't imagine what a headache that would be.<br />
<br />
Egad - the sheer fact that we're discussing this is just depressing.<br />
<br />
Shadrak<br />
62 shaman<br />
Ayonae Ro</p>
	
	
	
	
	
