	<p>Here's how it will play out...<br />
Step 1:    SOE barters sales in-game to ensure integrity<br />
.... time passes .....<br />
Step 2:    SOE removes limitations on no-drop items when barted through them  (sales sky-rocket)<br />
..... time passes and its even harder than it is now to get enough people online to raid .....<br />
Step 3:    SOE offers pre-leveled characters<br />
.....  more time passes:   game becomes like Planetside<br />
<br />
End result:   Game remains popular with all 65's running about doing raids, PVP, quests, etc   Focus becomes like Planetside with primarily open raids<br />
<br />
Nightmare scenario or reality?  Sounds to me like an excellent (from a business standpoint) way to phase out EQ yet remain profitable.  Will the bean counters win over historical gameplay?   (Check out UO sometime so see how thats playing out.....)<br />
-- Sharden (Morden Rasp)</p>
	
	
	
	
	
