	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>A company's job is to make money.  I don't see faulting a company for trying to keep it's employees paid and provide it's customers with the products and services they want to keep them buying "your" product as opposed to a competitor's product.<br />
<br />
Yantis/IGE is a competitor.  There was some sort of lawsuit a while back with Mythic and DAoC where people won and set a precident that folks *could* buy and sell the time they spent acquiring in-game items, or whatever, and that was a service that a person could provide to another person, and basically trying to go after it legally gets really sticky since that precident is already there, and most courts see time spent as the person behind the keyboard's time... they're not into video games and pixels and little electronic men.  They're into Frankie sat logged into this machine for 800 hours to achieve "this" ... and now he's marketing that "this" to someone else for the cost of 50 hours labor... it's tough.<br />
<br />
If I still had my account active, I would log in and vote "Yes" ... simply because I would rather support SOE in the hopes they can keep folks going than support folks like Yantis/IGE ... and SOE can DEMOLISH Yantis, and all the rest of the small-timers, this way, effortlessly.  I don't especially like the idea of some companies employing herds of kids or poverty-striken folks to farm plat all day, then sell it back.  Singapore is very difficult to get your money from if they don't come through on the trade.<br />
<br />
This would be safe, effective, and would help SOE kill upstarts like Yantis, et.al.  It <b>already</b> happens.  Why should SOE not be able to control it instead of trying to stop it.  It makes MILLIONS.  I'm pretty sure there's some Japanese VP or Board of Directors member somewhere that's noticed that too ... millions that AREN'T going back to SONY, on thier own product ... <br />
<br />
If I were a Japanese board of director, I'd be pretty upset about that lost potential revenue when the market is CLEARLY there and it would be virtually nothing for SOE to take the reins themselves...<br />
<br />
Do the math ... my bets are it's coming soon to a server near you.</p>
	
	
	
