<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Goldark</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Mystic<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Mar 2002<br />
	Location: London, UK
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>One thing about EQ is everyone is playing on relatively equal terms. As soon as people can start paying RL $$ for items it adds a large inbalance. Not to mention any sense of real achievement starts flying out the window.<br />
<br />
Yes, a significant minority are already buying stuff in game for RL $$. However, that is NO reason to make it official. Thats like saying "Well, quite a few people take cocaine, we might as well make it legal as we can't stop it". <br />
<br />
It'll harm the in-game economy more than it is already. Why sell items for pp when you can get RL $$ for them? At the moment I happily give away ornate patterns to good friends. Would I still do that knowing I can safely, legitimately sell them for RL $$? Probably not.<br />
<br />
Arguments about ninja-looting are bad enough at the moment, but at least you can sit back and say "Its just a game". But once you put real monetary value to things, well its a whole new ball game.<br />
<br />
I voted NO. You might have guessed <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
