<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Blazz</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Fateseer<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Sep 2003<br />
	Location: Upstate, NY
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I think the thing some people are missing is that this is NOT SOE selling items to players. It is merely SOE offering to moderate the RL exchange of items for dollars. The regluar rules still apply, you cannot sell no-drop (except on FV), you cannot sell flags, etc etc, unless you are offering entire accounts.<br />
<br />
Two dangers I see on this path though, and neither has anything to do with stupid CC# arguements. <br />
<br />
Problem #1. What is to stop the mega-hardcore elite (or anyone, actually) from PLing characters on accounts SOLELY for the purpose of selling them. Would be a simple matter to get them flagged up, a few "probably would rot anyway" items, and BAM put it up for sale. I realize this type of thing is probably being done now, but the scale is probably small. After all, it IS still against the EULA. However, once SOE puts their "stamp of approval" on this type of activity, the door would be open for this to become a legitimate "business". Hell, I might actually go into this business myself, why not. SOE says its OK. How much is a Time-flagged Rogue with 10 Time items worth? Don't even need the EP flags to get to Time, just 85% them in and loot the God items. <br />
<br />
Problem #2. What is the next logical step? Think hard people . . . YUP! You guessed it. SOE THEMSELVES selling items. I can picture it now. Merchants in the Bazaar, with names over their heads like "Velious Quest Items" and a Blessed Coldain Prayer Shawl, only $49.99 (just enter your credit card # in the box). Next up, Luclin Weapons! Emp Sword, $29.99, PoP Weapons, SEWS, $79.99. How UBER do you want to be? Well, how much cash you got?<br />
<br />
While I am against sites like Player Auctions and Yantis's trash, having SOE put a stamp of approval on RL cash-for-gear is a poison pill and would be bad for the game. Let the fringe element buy pp and gear if they want too, leave Yantis alone. Its really NOT that huge a deal right now (expcept for bugged crap like we had a couple months ago). But the INSTANT SOE says "Its OK, we are changing the EULA" it becomes a MAJOR thing. Yantis-type sites will pop up ALL over. People will /auction IN GAME. That would just not be cool, not one bit.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=639568" target="_blank">Blazz, 70 Troll Shaman, Bertoxx</a><br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=661668" target="_blank">Bleys, 56 High Elf Paladin, Bertoxx</a><br />
[size=1]I lamented that I had no shoes, until I met a man with no feet.<br />
