<tr>
	<td class="alt2" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>kiztent</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Disciple<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2003<br />
	
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Blazz</b><br /><i>Problem #1. What is to stop the mega-hardcore elite (or anyone, actually) from PLing characters on accounts SOLELY for the purpose of selling them. Would be a simple matter to get them flagged up, a few "probably would rot anyway" items, and BAM put it up for sale. I realize this type of thing is probably being done now, but the scale is probably small.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Not probably, certainly.  When I first moved to Legends there was a huge shakeup in the officership of Township Rebellion over ebaying the guild bank with the then guild leader leaving in disgrace.  Plus Leviathan had a group of people from Veeshan who were in a PL and sell ring.  They'd create accounts on SH, buy cheap lewtz, PL em to 65, grab some rot loots then send em back and auction em off.<br />
<br />
I've seen people that refuse to use anything they haven't looted themselves. I've known people that have put a Blade of Carnage on the credit card.  Heck, I don't know any personally, but I'm sure there are people out there that have cybered (and more) for loot.<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Blazz</b><br /><i>Problem #2. What is the next logical step? Think hard people . . . YUP! You guessed it. SOE THEMSELVES selling items.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Yeah, just like they were going to do that when they open the Legends server.  I'm sure everyone remembers the funny photoshopped screenshot with the graphic asking you to enter your CC to loot the Mylrokar's dagger.  Except they didn't do that on Legends (at least they hadn't started in Feb when I left). Heck, maybe Legends would be less of a ghost town if they did start selling loot for cold hard cash.<br />
<br />
All Sony is doing is getting the ability to control something they are going to get grief over if it goes wrong.  That is, if you send someone some money for loot and they scam you, what's your first reaction? Yea, petition. Then when the GM says they can't do anything you rant and rave about what a bunch of sorry bastards Sony's customer support has. Sony, it's pretty obvious, can't *stop* the selling of items.  So they may as well supervise it as best they can and try to stop scammers.<br />
<br />
So yes, I voted yes.<br />
<br />
I'm not going to feel like my accomplishments are any less because people choose to buy gear and Sony helps them not get ripped off (and the only real accomplishment I have is playing the game for 3 years while still enjoying it and meeting some good friends - selling gear won't change that).  I play for fun.  Sure I'd love to not have a job and raid and have a bigger e-penis.  Except that's not true. I like my paycheck more than I like to get my unbuffed HP to 7k or whatever.</p>
	
	
	
